        "steps": [
            {
                "description": "**Crust**"
            },
            {
                "description": "Preheat oven to 400 degrees fahrenheit. Butter a 9\" springform or pie pan."
            },
            {
                "description": "In a food processor, crush Oreo cookies or brownies. Add the melted butter and sugar. (I omitted the sugar and butter because my brownies were very moist already-- not at all crumbly). Press into the bottom of the prepared pan and bake for 10 minutes. Let cool completely."
            },
            {
                "description": "**Mousse**"
            },
            {
                "description": "Melt chocolate, stirring often, until smooth. Add vanilla and stir."
            },
            {
                "description": "In the bowl of a stand mixer, beat butter for 1 minute on medium speed. Add sugar and beat for 4 minutes on medium speed. Add chocolate and beat until incorporated."
            },
            {
                "description": "Add 2 eggs and beat for 3 minutes. Add 3rd egg and beat for 3 more minutes."
            },
            {
                "description": "In a separate bowl, whip cream for 4 minutes, or until stiff peaks form. Fold whipped cream and mousse together until it's completely incorporated."
            },
            {
                "description": "Spread evenly on cooled crust."
            },
            {
                "description": "**Whipped Cream**"
            },
            {
                "description": "In a bowl, combine cream, sugar, and vanilla. Whip until stiff peaks form. Pipe onto the pie or spread it evenly however you desire."
            },
